OL,3,CMinimum age for train drivers to be
OL,4,Clowered to 18 amid shortage
OL,6,FAmong other nations that have lowered
OL,7,Fthe age for train drivers are France,
OL,8,FGermany, the Netherlands and
OL,9,FSwitzerland, according to the DfT.
OL,11,FTransport for London opened up its
OL,12,Ftrain driver apprenticeships on the
OL,13,FUnderground to 18-year-olds in 2007.
OL,15,FTraining to become a driver of
OL,16,Fmainline trains generally takes
OL,17,Fbetween one and two years.
OL,19,FThe DfT said there are several steps
OL,20,Fbefore the minimum age can be lowered.
